  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Defence Education - Building Integrity for Senior Leaders</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Building Integrity for Senior Leaders (BISL) Course is focused at the One- and Two-star level (military and civilian officials from the wider defence and security sector) to examine the key aspects of leadership and change management in addressing the risk of corruption within the defence and security sector in: finance, acquisition and procurement, human resource management and on operations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the course is to enhance the awareness of the risks of corruption and of the measures than can be used to reduce the risk of its effects within defence. The course objectives are to: - Raise understanding of the challenges posed by corruption. - Appreciate the risks within Defence and Security sector acquisition, finance and HR. - Recognise the corruption risks on operations and during conflict resolution. - Assess the importance of leadership and strategic communications in challenging and changing behaviours.</narrative>
  </description>
